question: Calculate the average revenue per paying user (ARPU) over the last quarter
sql: SELECT SUM(p.trans_amount_decimal) / COUNT(DISTINCT c.merchant_user_id) AS ARPU FROM subscription_payment_details p JOIN subscription_contract_v2 c ON p.subscription_id = c.subscription_id WHERE DATE(p.created_date) >= '2025-04-01' AND p.status = 'ACTIVE'

question: What was the average revenue per user for the last 3 months?
sql: SELECT SUM(p.trans_amount_decimal) / COUNT(DISTINCT c.merchant_user_id) AS ARPU FROM subscription_payment_details p JOIN subscription_contract_v2 c ON p.subscription_id = c.subscription_id WHERE DATE(p.created_date) >= DATE_SUB(CURDATE(), INTERVAL 90 DAY) AND p.status = 'ACTIVE'

question: Compare subscribers with more than 1 and more than 2 subscriptions
sql:
SELECT 'More than 1 Subscriptions' as category, COUNT(*) as value 
FROM (SELECT merchant_user_id FROM subscription_contract_v2 GROUP BY merchant_user_id HAVING COUNT(*) > 1) t1
UNION ALL
SELECT 'More than 2 Subscriptions' as category, COUNT(*) as value  
FROM (SELECT merchant_user_id FROM subscription_contract_v2 GROUP BY merchant_user_id HAVING COUNT(*) > 2) t2

question: How many new subscriptions did we get this month
sql: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM subscription_contract_v2 WHERE DATE(subcription_start_date) >= DATE_SUB(CURDATE(), INTERVAL 1 MONTH)

question: show them them according to the dates they happened
sql: SELECT DATE(subcription_start_date) as subscription_date, COUNT(*) as num_subscriptions FROM subscription_contract_v2 GROUP BY subscription_date ORDER BY subscription_date
improvement_suggestion: i only asked for this month which is june 2025

question: show them them according to the dates they happened
sql: SELECT DATE(subcription_start_date) as subscription_date, COUNT(*) AS num_subscriptions FROM subscription_contract_v2 WHERE DATE(subcription_start_date) BETWEEN '2025-06-01' AND '2025-06-30' GROUP BY DATE(subcription_start_date)
